Clonal relationships among endometrial glands that share rhizome structures

Markdown file to present the methods to examine clonal relationships among endometrial glands that share rhizome structures. Before you start the following analyses, please convert the corresponding excel source data files to tab-delimited text files. The source data files are provided in our paper (Yamaguchi et al.Nat Commun in press).

Load libraries

library(dplyr)
library(ggplot2)
library(tidyr)

Visualize clonal relationships among endometrial glands that share rhizome structures

mafData_long <- mafData %>% gather(sample, mutant_allele_frequency, -chr, -pos, -ref, -alt, -cluster, factor_key=TRUE)
mafData_long$sample2 <- sub("S41_", "", mafData_long$sample)
mafData_long$sample3 <- factor(mafData_long$sample2, levels=c("G1", "G2", "G3", "G4", "G5", "G6", "G7", "G8", "G9", "G10", "G11", "G12", "G13"))

clone_colors <- c("#e27f8c", "#d7ebf9", "#f4c6f4", "#e1f9aa", "#f8e780", "#80cff2", "#fff780", "#80cdca", "#b3dd4b", "#e8b58a", "#b2ffff")

temp_data <- filter(mafData_long, sample3 %in% c("G1", "G2", "G3", "G4", "G5", "G6", "G7"))

p_gr1 <- ggplot(data=temp_data, aes(x=1, y=mutant_allele_frequency, fill=cluster))
p_gr1 <- p_gr1 + geom_hline(yintercept=0, color="gray")
p_gr1 <- p_gr1 + geom_hline(yintercept=0.25, color="gray")
p_gr1 <- p_gr1 + geom_hline(yintercept=0.5, color="gray")
p_gr1 <- p_gr1 + geom_hline(yintercept=0.75, color="gray")
p_gr1 <- p_gr1 + geom_hline(yintercept=1, color="gray")
p_gr1 <- p_gr1 + geom_jitter(height=0, width=0.1, size=2.5, shape=21)
p_gr1 <- p_gr1 + facet_grid(sample3 ~ cluster)
p_gr1 <- p_gr1 + scale_fill_manual(values=clone_colors, name="")
p_gr1 <- p_gr1 + scale_y_continuous(breaks=c(0, 0.5, 1))
p_gr1 <- p_gr1 + xlab("")
p_gr1 <- p_gr1 + ylab("Mutant allele frequency")
p_gr1 <- p_gr1 + ggtitle("Group 1")
p_gr1 <- p_gr1 + theme(
  axis.ticks=element_blank(), 
  axis.text.x=element_blank(), 
  axis.text.y=element_text(size=10, colour="black"), 
  axis.title=element_text(size=15), 
  plot.title=element_text(size=15, hjust=0.5), 
  strip.text.x=element_text(size=15, colour="white"), 
  strip.text.y=element_text(size=15, colour="white", angle=0), 
  strip.background=element_rect(fill="black"),
  panel.background=element_rect(fill="white", colour="black", size=0.5, linetype="solid"),
  panel.grid.major=element_blank(),
  panel.grid.minor=element_blank(),
  legend.position="none",
  plot.margin=margin(5.5, 5.5, 5.5, 5.5, "pt"))

plot(p_gr1)

Visualize clonal relationships among bifurcating endometrial glands

subData_long <- subData %>% gather(sample, mutant_allele_frequency, -type, -chr, -pos, -ref, -alt, factor_key=TRUE)
subData_long$sample2 <- sub("S41_", "", subData_long$sample)
temp_data <- subData_long[subData_long$type == "shared_3_5", ]

p_35 <- ggplot(data=temp_data, aes(x=sample2, y=mutant_allele_frequency)) 
p_35 <- p_35 + geom_hline(aes(yintercept=0.5), colour="black", linetype="dashed")
p_35 <- p_35 + geom_boxplot(aes(fill=sample2), width=0.75, size=1)
p_35 <- p_35 + scale_fill_manual(values=c("#f15a24", "#662d91", "#d4145a"))
p_35 <- p_35 + xlab("")
p_35 <- p_35 + ylab("Mutant allele frequency")
p_35 <- p_35 + ggtitle("Shared between G3 and G5")
p_35 <- p_35 + ylim(0, 1)
p_35 <- p_35 + theme(
  axis.text.x=element_text(size=20, colour="black"), 
  axis.text.y=element_text(size=20, colour="black"), 
  axis.title=element_text(size=20), 
  plot.title=element_text(size=20, hjust=0.5),
  panel.grid.major=element_blank(),
  panel.border=element_rect(colour="gray", fill=NA),
  panel.background=element_blank(),
  axis.ticks=element_line(colour="gray"),
  legend.position="none")

plot(p_35)
